<h1>Help</h1>

You can browse all existing animons and if you can find one which isn't listed, you can add them and look after them!

<h2>Classification</h2>
Animons are grouped and classified using scientific classification, or <%= link_to 'taxonomy', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taxonomy_(biology)' %>.
For example, here are the taxonomy ranks of the red fox:
<ul>
<li><b>Phylum:</b> Chordate</li>
<li><b>Class:</b> Mammal</li>
<li><b>Order:</b> Carnivoran</li>
<li><b>Family:</b> Canid</li>
<li><b>Genus:</b> True fox</li>
<li><b>Species:</b> Red fox</li>
</ul>

There are even more possible ranks:
<%= Taxon::RANKS.join(' > ') %>
<br/>
If you want to add an animal, make sure to add it to the right one!
<br/>
Hint: there is a lot of help available online, starting with <%= link_to 'Wikipedia', 'https://www.wikipedia.org'%>.

<h2>Anidex</h2>
In the <%= link_to 'Anidex', browse_index_path %>, you can browse all animons by taxonomy rank. Also, from each animon
you can navigate to all related animons.

<h2>Add a new animon</h2>
If your favourite animon is not there, you can add it yourself and start looking after it!
<br/>
Look for its scientific name and its classification. Click <%= link_to 'New', new_taxon_path %> to create the classification and the animon
(they are both called <i>taxons</i>). Enter the information and click <b>Create taxon</b>!

